column3: i attracted people who were running away from themselves. i was as well. i embrace and forgive myself as it was the best i could do then.

column1: any other mamas feel like they've run a marathon before 9am? drained a day's worth of energy before you've ever left the house?
here‚Äôs our am jam these days:
üñ§refusal to eat the breakfast (despite it being gobbled up the day before)
üñ§shrieks of one sitting ""too close"" to the other
üñ§ripping clothes off as soon as they are put on.
üñ§scrambling to get ready while whining sticky fingers pull on my leg.
üñ§screams as they push against the carseat buckling.
the ironic part is that every morning
i sit. i pray. i write things i'm grateful for. i drink lemon water and eat my green protein. i'm in my flow!
yet every morning there seems to be a storm waiting downstairs for me. .
and as i'm on my way to work
column2: i feel this giant crash and burn.

column1: it feels as if i've lost myself.
and find myself wondering if other families have the same mornings.
i find myself apologizing to my unborn baby for the surge of adrenaline that has pumped thru my womb. .
i find myself wondering how the hell i'm going to find the energy to make it to the end of the day.
this is not a cry for advice or sympathy.
i wanted to post a #reallife moment because
column2: shit. i love inspirational and high vibes
column3: but sometimes you just gotta be real. .

column1: 56101;instagram;2019-01-29 15:49:13;FALSE;"*proceed with caution* the attached tweet is not from a parody account. this was a real tweet from a real person. there are so many things to dissect in these tweets but i want to address tomi‚Äôs questioning of kamala advocating for the #metoo movement. it is extremely reckless and unfortunate to associate infidelity with sexual assault. this is clearly a false equivalent. i surmise that tomi is using the donald trump playbook of false equivalence and in this instance
column2: it undermines true victims of sexual assault by alluding or flat out stating that any act of sexual assault is either consensual and/or brought on by the victim.

column1: what i am having a hard time wrapping my mind around is why tomi is so compelled to go after kamala. after getting hit with the ‚Äúdon‚Äôt come for me unless i send for you‚Äù from cardi b
column2: tomi still proceeded to make this comment. while both women come from different backgrounds
column3: they both share the burden of being a woman. this leads me to believe that tomi a.) does not have the wherewithal to understand what sexual assault is and/or b.) her attacks are so deep rooted in racism that any thoughtful comment that she attempts to make only shines a bigger light on her bigotry.

column1: the other thought that i have with this is how movements pushed by black people get marginalized or outright discredited. i‚Äôm not sure tomi picked the right one as #metoo includes people of all races but we saw this with a significantly more fragile movement: black lives matter. this came on strong due to multiple instances of black people being gunned down
column3: people took ‚Äúblack lives matter‚Äù to be ‚Äúonly black lives matter‚Äù instead of ‚Äúblack lives matter too(as well-for those who appreciate grammar)‚Äù. i don‚Äôt think that people like tomi will be able to diminish #metoo because the statement in itself aligns with inclusion

column5: her actions failed to make sense to me and i was left guessing. sumanth however

column2: we are dedicating our week to child sex trafficking prevention and awareness. if you are in or around the metro atlanta region
column3: we need you to be on the lookout for possible child sex trafficking victims. this includes in and around local hotels and motels
column4: as well as truck stops and residential neighborhoods. truck stops are prime locations for sex trafficking. they serve as the ""business location"" for traffickers and they are the transfer point for victims to be moved from one state or country to another. residential properties being used more frequently because they draw less attention than hotels and motels. be on the lookout for random cars pulling up in your neighborhood with underage kids inside
column5: as well as . an increase in random visitors entering a home in your neighborhood. rental services such as air bnb allow traffickers to set up an operation within hours and clear out just as quick. major events like the super bowl draw people from all over the world who are looking to buy sex with children. if you are a victim or suspect that a child may be a victim of sex trafficking
column6: please call 911 or call the national human trafficking resource center at 1-888-373-7888 for help. all victims of slavery and human trafficking have rights and are protected by international

column1: 56182;instagram;2019-01-28 16:13:43;FALSE;"mountains show us what the earth is capable of being on its own.
the earth evolves and changes magnificently without our help.

the same goes for each of us. we can evolve without the molds others have for us because we are the experts about ourselves. we just need to uncover the parts of us we hid out of injury or hurt. we need connection again. sometimes connection is with our environment
column4: our community... mostly tho - it is with ourselves.

column1: who were you before your heart was hurt? who were you before the first time you felt dark sadness creep over you? i know you were someone else before you were raped or fondled. i know you were someone else before your first black eye or broken arm. i know you were someone else before your first love or first heartbreak.
who were you before the world told you who you should be? where were your mountains before someone wanted roads?
this is why i teach yoga.

column2: i lost all my friends. all. i was hated. but i didn‚Äôt care because my face was radiant. i was not covered in shame. god will always reach out to you w comfort. you just hafta listen...

column1: 56274;instagram;2019-01-29 12:32:03;FALSE;"we present to you our next speaker for polity 2019.
swati maliwal is an indian activist and politician. she is the current chairperson of delhi commission for women.
maliwal started her first term as chairperson of delhi commission for women in july 2015. at that time
column2: she was an aam aadmi party leader. her tenure in the position was extended for another three years in july 2018. she is the youngest person to hold the role of commissioner for women.
she went on a 10-day hunger strike which started on april 13. she had several demands
column3: including the passage of an ordinance requiring the death penalty for individuals who rape children under age 12
column4: recruiting police under united nations standards and demanding accountability of the police. her strike took place during a series of protests surrounding two alleged rapes of girls ages 16 and 8. members of an organization
column5: rape roko (stop rape) were supportive of maliwal.

column1: she would be speaking on the topic - politics around #metoo at polity 2019.

column1: 56306;instagram;2019-01-29 11:31:42;FALSE;"it took me a few days to calm down and share what actually is a well written article by angela baura. (thank you angela!!) the digital version has a different headline and it threw me off completely. i was horrified. i felt victimized. but after a couple of days
column2: i decided to look at it again and i looked past the headline and saw the story for what it is. it is an article about finding yourself post rape and becoming who you want to be.

column1: the weird thing is i didn't even know the article was out on friday evening. i was grabbing a bite when i got a call from a complete stranger who read my article and he shared his tragic story with me. first i was confused if he was actually speaking to the right person cause i hadn't seen my article but after that was confirmed
column2: i was grateful that he reached out and so many others have since.

column1: honestly i don't know how it helps by speaking to me but if it gives people hope that this will pass as in you will get through it because i did and i know every victim can. then regardless of how uncomfortable i initially felt
column2: this is worth it. to all the victims out there
column3: you are a survivor and you can recreate the person you want to become and i am a living proof.

column1: i hope to continue to inspire people and do what it takes to curb sexual violence.

column2: a girl's faith is about my journey and the beautiful relationship i had with my beloved grandmother which will be out on feb 27th on amazon. support me and end incest as 5% will go directly to them.

column2: one of my friend called me. he was has been my classmate and gradually became my friend. he told me that something was wrong. he was not feeling good. i understood the matter as i knew that he was sad because of homesickness. when he came back to college hostel after spending more than two weeks at his home
column3: he was totally suffering from homesickness.

column2: ""what happened?"" he said that there was no one in the hostel and there was nothing to do. he mentioned that he attended just one class after coming back but didn't mention that he was feeling sad because he was totally trapped in that homesickness. i tried asking him and after asking so many times
column3: he finally said that he was missing his home.

column1: i really wondered why he took this much time to open up to this? why is it hard for him to say those things? why didn't he tell me earlier (very beginning when we started talking). why a boy is not supposed to feel that way and why is he not supposed to share those feelings to anyone? why didn't we ever tell them that they can feel anything
column3: for anyone? why didn't we ever tell them that they are not meant to be rock? i wonder why!

5) when you think about the event/situation

column1: 56586;instagram;2019-01-29 03:32:55;FALSE;"each day we make a choice as to how we want to react to the experiences in our life.  we can succumb to the depression
column3: and other unhelpful emotions‚Äîor we can choose to rise and allow the negative experiences to make us stronger and better people.

column1: for years i endured terrible physical abuse
column3: and later it became obvious‚Äî large amounts of infidelity.  my decision to ignore red flags from a person i loved would ultimately bring such sadness into my life.  but i now realize i never actually loved who he was
column4: i loved the illusion he created
column5: his true colors would only show when he was accused of rape and tried to force me to ‚Äúclear his name‚Äù in an attempt to publicly maintain the facade.

column1: .  my sense of self worth had been so degraded that i believed no one would ever love me and i deserved every fist he threw into my head and every insult to my being and what made me happy.  however
column2: i broke free of the cycle of abuse and decided it was better to be alone and love myself than to love someone who only used me
column4: for their own personal gain.  here i stand

column1: dragged my bike and trainer through a freaking blizzard (so bad schools were closed!) and some of the coldest weather chicago has ever experienced to my older son‚Äôs soccer practice to get some work done! üí™üèΩüëäüèΩüö¥üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è i figure if i have 90 minutes there i may as well start doing bike training there a few days a week. so i set up shop in a corner and got it done while my little guy ran around and fed me fritos üòÇ

and earlier in the day i squeezed in my run! i‚Äôll write a whole post on my new training and link my beginner half marathon training plan too. but if you read my post from yesterday you probably better understand why i hit a massive block and running has been really hard for me to get back into. üôèüèΩ anyways....i‚Äôm back and in 8 months and one freaking day i‚Äôm going to run a damn marathon after a 2.4 mile swim and 116 mile bike ride. (chattanooga has a longer bike course üòâ)!!!! but today
column2: i‚Äôm still building my confidence and mental strength back up and did another 2x8 mins with a 4 min walk between sets. which is the proper day 1 of my training plan. üëäüèΩ i‚Äôll get there. slow and steady and i‚Äôll add consistent wins the race right? and winning to me is crossing that finish line smiling and empowered that i took back the sport of triathlon that i love so much üôèüèΩüí™üèΩü•∞üñ§

column1: this time it is more personal than ever and you‚Äôre probably beginning to see why. i plan on sharing every freaking struggle and triumph along these next 8 months with you. to show that healing exists
column2: love wins and my passion is back and burning hotter than ever before. üî•üëäüèΩ 2019 is the year we all step into our full power
column3: kick some ass and have a freaking blast doing it! who‚Äôs with me?!? üôåüèΩ

column1: 56745;instagram;2019-01-29 01:01:26;FALSE;"please welcome cristina garcia to the wosc family üôåüèæ
she is the founder of ‚Äúshe grows we grow‚Äù -- a community addressing issues of identity
column2: voice and power. she is specifically centering women of color (woc). her goal is to create a space that explores all of the richness and beauty of woc multidimensional identities.
her vision is to build a global movement of women of color who define and create their own identity
column3: on their own terms‚Ä¶. boldly and unapologetically.

column1: some of her major influences have always been those working in the trenches around social justice issues
column4: and her family who has always supported her work. leaders she admires the most are movers & shakers
column7: and all those who are not afraid to speak truth to power.

column1: cristina‚Äôs friends would describe her as passionate
column4: determined and a fighter for what she believes in.

column1: she just hosted her first event in long beach called ""exploring our true self in 2019"" and she also presented at the women's empowerment expo.
other major projects include launching a podcast as part of the ‚Äúshe grows we grow‚Äù platform

column2: i was almost 302ed. i had a breakdown when i had realized i had been denied yet again for social security. something i have been trying for years to get and i keep getting denied. i left my house in a panicked stooper with so many feelings of how unfair it is that my #assaulter can have social security
column5: and public housing help while still working 40 hours a week under the table. and i can barely make it through 3 days a week of a medial job but i get denied for everything. i want to give up. i am afraid of what this person is capable of because of their #schizophrenia diagnosis which is why i have not made any reports. i don't want to hear about #empowerment and #metoo and that it will give me #peace to file charges. pressing charges doesn't change the fact that i have #posttraumaticstressdisorder from this now and will for the rest of my life. pressing charges won't stop my #flashbacks. facing the person in a courtroom will cause me irreversible damage to my already dwindling #mentalhealth. and there's the gray area of if i do file charges and we go through the whole process they could still be found not guilty. which is the most terrifying part because this person lives 528 feet from my front door. i have had to see their vehicle every single day since my #assault  almost a year ago.  i am trying to hold on and wait for the grass to grow again because i missed it last year due to me developing #agrophobia and spending my whole #summer in my basement trying to forget everything. next time you want tell a woman she is lying
